ch.iserver.ace.algorithm.test
Interface ScenarioBuilder

All Known Implementing Classes:
DefaultScenarioBuilder
public interface ScenarioBuilder

This interface contains the elementary operations needed to construct a scenario. It is based on the builder pattern (see GOF).

Method Detail

init

void init(String initialState,
          String finalState)
Initializes the builder and passes in the initial state and the expected final state.

Parameters:
initialState - the initial state at all sites
finalState - the expected final state

startSite

void startSite(String siteId)
Notifies the builder of the start of a new site to process. Calls to startSite and endSite must be executed in proper sequence. Most notably, after calling startSite this method cannot be executed again until endSite is called.

Parameters:
siteId - the identifier of the site
Throws:
ScenarioException - in case of errors

addReception

void addReception(String opRef)
Adds the reception of an operation to the current site. The current site is the last site for which startSite was called. This method must be called within startSite/endSite.

Parameters:
opRef - the operation to be received
Throws:
ScenarioException - in case of errors

Parameters:
id - the id of this event
operation - the generated operation
Throws:
ScenarioException - in case of errors

endSite

Throws:
